[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] This feature is well established and works across many devices and browser versions.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] It’s been available across browsers since January 2020.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] The **`ShadowRoot`** interface of the Shadow DOM API is the root node of a DOM subtree that is rendered separately from a document's main DOM tree.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] You can retrieve a reference to an element's shadow root using its `Element.shadowRoot` property, provided it was created using `Element.attachShadow()` with the `mode` option set to `open`.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] Returns the `Element` within the shadow tree that has focus.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] Add an array of constructed stylesheets to be used by the shadow DOM subtree.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] These may be shared with other DOM subtrees that share the same parent `Document` node, and the document itself.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] A boolean that indicates whether the shadow root is clonable.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] Returns the `CustomElementRegistry` object associated with this shadow root, or `null` if one has not been set.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] A boolean that indicates whether the shadow root delegates focus if a non-focusable node is selected.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] The element that's currently in full screen mode for this shadow tree.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] Returns a reference to the DOM element the `ShadowRoot` is attached to.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] Sets or returns a reference to the DOM tree inside the `ShadowRoot`.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] The mode of the `ShadowRoot`, either `open` or `closed`.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] This defines whether or not the shadow root's internal features are accessible from JavaScript.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] Returns the `Element` within the shadow tree that is currently being presented in picture-in-picture mode.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] Returns the `Element` set as the target for mouse events while the pointer is locked.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] `null` if lock is pending, pointer is unlocked, or if the target is in another tree.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] A nullable string value that indicates the effective target of any element reference made against the shadow host from outside the host element.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] The value should be the ID of an element inside the shadow DOM.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] If set, target references to the host element from outside the shadow DOM will cause the referenced target element to become the effective target of the reference to the host element.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] A boolean that indicates whether the shadow root is serializable.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] A serializable shadow root inside an element will be serialized by `Element.getHTML()` or `ShadowRoot.getHTML()` when its `options.serializableShadowRoots` parameter is set `true`.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] This is set when the shadow root is created.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] Returns a string containing the type of slot assignment, either `manual` or `named`.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] Returns a `StyleSheetList` of `CSSStyleSheet` objects for stylesheets explicitly linked into, or embedded in a shadow tree.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] Returns an array of all `Animation` objects currently in effect, whose target elements are descendants of the shadow tree.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] Returns a `Selection` object representing the range of text selected by the user, or the current position of the caret.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] Returns the topmost element at the specified coordinates.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] Returns an array of all elements at the specified coordinates.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] Provides an XSS-safe method to parse and sanitize a string of HTML into a `DocumentFragment`, which then replaces the existing tree in the shadow DOM.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] Parses a string of HTML into a document fragment, without sanitization, which then replaces the shadowroot's original subtree.
[src:shadow-dom-deep/api-shadowroot] The HTML string may include declarative shadow roots, which would be parsed as template elements the HTML was set using `ShadowRoot.innerHTML`.
